		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.jwz.org/blog/2014/09/why-we-believe-apple/#comment-157553">
			3 days ago at 7:52 am</a>		</div>

		<span class='herpc'><p>Trust them to do what?</p>
<p>Where I'm from, people don't keep cash under their mattresses, they deposit cash in banks. If they own jewelry and gold coins, they prefer putting them in bank safety deposit boxes to under their mattress, or in a deposit box from someone random in the cheap part of town. The use credit cards, which is basically the bank telling the merchant they will get paid, and the consumer that they will get what they paid for or they can reverse the charges.</p>
<p>Trust is what a bank is selling. </p>
<p>I trust them to maximize their big income stream and high fees, by not absconding with my deposits or safe deposit box.</p>
</span>
