		<span class='herpc'><p>Because, unlike Facebook, Google, and even John Gilmore, Apple has never ever lied to me.</p>
<p>It's that simple. </p>
<p>40 years of honesty builds a lot of credibility.</p>
<p>Call me a fanboy if you will.</p>
<p>All that said, there's always levels of "secure".  It's a grey area.  I trust iOS 8 two orders of magnitude more than I do anything involving google, but I would still, for things that are really important, use an OS more under my control.</p>
<p>But for my phone?  Yeah, glad that Apple's around to at least push back on the NSA (unlike Google, Facebook, Amazon, Microsoft, et. al.)</p>
